---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
    title="About — Pencil Ready"
    description="Pencil Ready is a free, ad-free math worksheet generator for primary-school students. Configure a worksheet, download as PDF, print."
    canonical="https://pencilready.com/about/"
>
    <div class="p-4 md:p-8 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
        <article
            class="rounded-xl border bg-card text-card-foreground shadow p-6 md:p-10 space-y-8"
        >
            <header class="space-y-2">
                <h1
                    class="text-3xl font-semibold pb-0 border-b-2 border-pencil-no-2"
                >
                    About Pencil Ready
                </h1>
                <p class="text-muted-foreground text-lg">
                    Free, printable math worksheets for 1st–6th grade.
                </p>
            </header>

            <nav
                aria-label="On this page"
                class="text-sm text-muted-foreground"
            >
                <ul class="flex flex-wrap gap-x-4 gap-y-1">
                    <li>
                        <a
                            href="#why-this-exists"
                            class="underline underline-offset-2 hover:text-primary"
                        >
                            Why this exists
                        </a>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <a
                            href="#using-the-worksheets"
                            class="underline underline-offset-2 hover:text-primary"
                        >
                            Using the worksheets
                        </a>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <a
                            href="#whats-inside"
                            class="underline underline-offset-2 hover:text-primary"
                        >
                            What's inside
                        </a>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <a
                            href="#open-source"
                            class="underline underline-offset-2 hover:text-primary"
                        >
                            Open source
                        </a>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <a
                            href="#whats-next"
                            class="underline underline-offset-2 hover:text-primary"
                        >
                            What's next
                        </a>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <a
                            href="#credits"
                            class="underline underline-offset-2 hover:text-primary"
                        >
                            Credits
                        </a>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </nav>

            <section id="why-this-exists" class="space-y-4 scroll-mt-8">
                <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Why this exists</h2>
                <p>
                    Pencil Ready started as a tool for one 5th grader learning
                    long division in Oslo. Her dad — a software engineer —
                    raised an eyebrow at modern math-teaching methods that
                    skewed heavily digital and embraced AI. He grew up learning
                    math step by step, skill by skill, reinforced through
                    repetition. Wanting the same practice surface for his
                    daughter, he turned to online worksheet generators. Most of
                    these were loaded down with ads, required users to log in,
                    or had restrictive usage limits. They weren't designed to
                    meet what seemed like a clear and worthy mission:
                </p><p>
                    Make math drilling simple and accessible for everyone.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Pencil Ready is the answer: a single page that generates a
                    clean, printable PDF on demand, with no ads, no cookies, no
                    login, and no usage limits.
                </p>
                <p>
                    So, a guy who loves math built what he needed to help his
                    kid learn fundamental skills, but also to support other
                    parents who need an online math resource that just works.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section id="using-the-worksheets" class="space-y-4 scroll-mt-8">
                <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Using the worksheets</h2>
                <p>
                    The PDFs you download from Pencil Ready are released under <a
                        href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/"
                        class="underline underline-offset-2 hover:text-primary"
                        rel="license noopener">Creative Commons BY 4.0</a
                    >. In plain English:
                </p>
                <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
                    <li>
                        <strong>Print as many as you need.</strong> A class set,
                        a stack for the staff room, a copy for every student in
                        your school — all fine.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Share them.</strong> Post on your classroom site,
                        drop into Google Classroom, hand off to a colleague,
                        email to a parent.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Edit them.</strong> Cross out problems, scribble
                        notes in the margins, scan and mark up. Once you print
                        a worksheet, it's yours to mark up however you like.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Use them at work.</strong> Tutors, after-school
                        programs, paid courses, printed workbooks — yes, this
                        includes commercial use.
                    </li>
                </ul>
                <p>
                    The one thing the license asks: if you <em>republish</em> the
                    worksheets — on a website, in a workbook, as part of a
                    curriculum package — credit Pencil Ready and link back to <a
                        href="https://pencilready.com"
                        class="underline underline-offset-2 hover:text-primary"
                        >pencilready.com</a
                    >. For everyday classroom use — print, hand out, recycle —
                    there's nothing else to think about.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section id="whats-inside" class="space-y-4 scroll-mt-8">
                <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">What's inside</h2>
                <p>
                    Every worksheet is generated server-side by a Rust program
                    that hands a curated description to <a
                        href="https://typst.app"
                        class="underline underline-offset-2 hover:text-primary"
                        >Typst</a
                    >, a modern typesetting system. Typst does the heavy lifting
                    of laying out digits, operators, brackets, and fraction bars
                    at pixel-perfect print quality. The result is embedded,
                    subsetted fonts and vector geometry — same output whether
                    you print it on A4 in Oslo or US Letter in Indiana.
                </p>
                <p>
                    The UI you're using now is Astro with a small React island
                    for the interactive configurator. Each worksheet type has
                    its own URL that's pre-rendered to HTML at build time, so
                    search engines (and any browser with JavaScript turned off)
                    can still read the page.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section id="open-source" class="space-y-4 scroll-mt-8">
                <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Open source</h2>
                <p>
                    The entire project — Rust generators, Typst templates, Astro
                    frontend — lives at <a
                        href="https://github.com/kung-foo/pencil-ready"
                        class="underline underline-offset-2 hover:text-primary"
                        rel="noopener">github.com/kung-foo/pencil-ready</a
                    >. The source code is released under the MIT license — clone
                    it, self-host it, fork it, or <a
                        href="https://github.com/kung-foo/pencil-ready/issues"
                        class="underline underline-offset-2 hover:text-primary"
                        rel="noopener">file an issue</a
                    > if you spot a bug or have a suggestion. PRs for new worksheet
                    types are welcome.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section id="whats-next" class="space-y-4 scroll-mt-8">
                <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">What's next</h2>
                <p>
                    The worksheet catalog grows when a new topic comes up in the
                    curriculum. Things currently on the list: decimal
                    arithmetic, order of operations, negative numbers, area and
                    perimeter, unit conversion.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section id="credits" class="space-y-4 scroll-mt-8">
                <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Credits</h2>
                <p>
                    Built with Rust, Typst, Astro, React, Tailwind, shadcn/ui,
                    and fly.io. Fonts: Roboto Slab (body), Fira Mono / Fira Code
                    (digits), Fira Math (operators), STIX Two Text (variables).
                    The rainbow heart is by my daughter.
                </p>
            </section>

            <div class="pt-4 border-t">
                <a
                    href="/"
                    class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-primary hover:underline underline-offset-4"
                >
                    ← Back to worksheets
                </a>
            </div>
        </article>
    </div>
</Layout>
